metadata.name: I'm Boring (Master)
metadata.description:
[Verse 1]  
Hey, I wanna break shit  
Just go apeshit, laugh as I tear it down  
Hey, No More safe shit  
MDMA in a cake, it's my birthday now

[Pre-Chorus]  
At 3 in the morning  
I’m always so ready for it  
But when I wake up to write my story  
I remember I’m boring

[Chorus]  
I would be a legend if I could  
Go out and tear apart the scene, go Hollywood  
But when I leave, it drags me back  
It comes without any warning  
I remember I’m boring  
Remember I'm boring

[Verse 2]  
Hey, I wanna make out  
With the takeout girl at the Charlie Browns  
Hey, We’ll be too loud  
Call for anarchy when they throw me out

[Pre-Chorus]  
At 3 in the morning  
I’m always so ready for it  
But when I wake up to write my story  
I remember-  
I remember I'm boring

[Chorus]  
I would be a legend if I could  
Go out and tear apart the scene, go Hollywood  
But when I leave, it drags me back  
It comes without any warning  
I remember-  
If I could find the high im looking for  
Get to The Otherside, of trying something more  
But when I dream, it drags me back  
It comes without any warning  
I remember-

[Bridge]  
I used to think that one day I’d give the best of me  
But eventually  
My normalcy caught up to me  
I’ll write a new story  
With no limits for me  
If I can ignore the warning  
And forget that I’m boring

[Outro]  
Forget that I’m boring  
Forget that I’m boring  
Forget that I’m boring  
I’m boring
